CD33

Description

Myeloid cell surface antigen CD33 (CD33). Sialic-acid-binding immunoglobulin-like lectin (Siglec) that plays a role in mediating cell-cell interactions and in maintaining immune cells in a resting state.


Clinical trials

NCT03638206 - Esophagus Cancer, Renal Carcinoma, Hepatoma, Lung Cancer, Mesothelioma, Ovarian Cancer, Pancreatic Cancer, Melanoma
